The suspense horror/dark fantasy story is set in Tokyo, which is haunted by mysterious "ghouls" who are devouring humans. People are gripped by the fear of these ghouls whose identities are masked in mystery. An ordinary college student named Kaneki encounters Rize, a girl who is an avid reader like him, at the café he frequents. Little does he realize that his fate will change overnight.
(Source: Anime News Network)
Mushoku Tensei: Isekai Ittara Honki Dasu Part 2

After the mysterious mana calamity, Rudeus Greyrat and his fierce student Eris Boreas Greyrat are teleported to the Demon Continent. There, they team up with their newfound companion Ruijerd Supardia—the former leader of the Superd's Warrior group—to form "Dead End," a successful adventurer party. Making a name for themselves, the trio journeys across the continent to make their way back home to Fittoa.
Following the advice he received from the faceless god Hitogami, Rudeus saves Kishirika Kishirisu, the Great Emperor of the Demon World, who rewards him by granting him a strange power. Now, as Rudeus masters the powerful ability that offers a number of new opportunities, it might prove to be more than what he bargained for when unexpected dangers threaten to hinder their travels.
(Source: MAL Rewrite)
Ao no Outline: Tensai no Egaku Sekai wo Bonjin ga Nurikaeru Houhou

"Fascinating" "Overwhelming" "Addictive" "Captivating"
Those are the reactions when people see her paintings.
As a high school student and aspiring artist, I desperately wanted to paint like her.
Yuri Kashiwazaki, the girl who is regarded a "genius," no matter what she draws.

"I just came by to see you. I only paint when I want to."

She is my childhood friend, at once the closest and furthest person to me. One day, she just stopped painting, but I remained in her shadow and continued to wield my paintbrush.

"I'm going to keep painting. I won't give up. I won't use talent as an excuse."

Until the day when Yuri starts painting again. Until the day she will admire my paintings.

This is the story of an ordinary boy who devotes his youth to art, to challenge a "genius."

(Source: Fantasia Bunko, translated)
